<br>
The Guide that I argued with suggested the Lake Rathe arena, but that would be a complete nightmare for a Newbie tournament. One other suggestion would be a circle of coppers in one of the less crowded flat zones, with each person dueling each other. But that completely cuts out team and free for all battles, which are great fun. <br>
<br>
Another problem experienced with this type of event is one of time. Not only was I up until about 2 AM running the thing (with time added for idiot interruptions) on what would have been a work night, but there were also people both in my guild and contestants who couldn't stay on long enough to get to their event. One way to alleviate this problem would be to have a week's worth of tourneys or so, with one or two level brackets per night. Some people will still have to leave, but this might ensure that we can get a larger number in per bracket.<br>
<br>
Also found that a lot of people will pre-register for the event and not show up. I don't think any of my preregistrants this time showed up, while in the last, we had maybe 3 or 4 out of 10-12.  But that doesn't cut down on the number of people who enter.<br>
<br>
